<concept id="concept_FAFDCB5BC3864E738EE94DFD0478CF59" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>About this Manual</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>This manual describes the basic tasks involved in the operation and maintenance of <ph product="oscm_ce"
                        ><ph conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Name"/> (<ph
                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>)</ph><ph
                    product="oscm_ee">FUJITSU Software Enterprise Service Catalog Manager, hereafter referred to as <ph
                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/></ph>.</p>
            <p>The manual is structured as follows: </p>
            <p>
                <table colsep="1" frame="all" rowsep="1">
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colname="col2" colnum="1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                        <colspec colname="col3" colnum="2" colwidth="1.3*"/>
                        <thead>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2">Chapter</entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Description</entry>
                            </row>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Introduction/c_Intro.xml"> </xref></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Describes <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    />, its containers and their communication, its architecture, organizations, users, roles, and authentication modes.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../GettingStarted/c_GettingStarted.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Describes how to access the <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                        /> administration portal, lists the initial steps to be performed after installing <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                        />, and shows how to start and stop the <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> containers.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../Configuration/c_Configuration.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes how to update the <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> and APP configuration settings, how to add a currency and a language, how to use and configure timers for automatic task processing, as well as how to manage platform-wide LDAP settings.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Monitoring/c_RegularIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3">Describes how to retrieve <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> logging information, how to configure the log level, as well as which data is subject to regular backups. In addition, it describes how to export the audit log data and how to check the load on the JMS queues.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../Organizations/c_Organizations.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes how to create and manage organizations, users, and OIDC tenants. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../Marketplace/c_ManageMP.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes how to create, update, delete, and customize marketplaces. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../Reports/c_Reports.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the reports available for operators in <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"/>.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../Billing/c_BillingPayment.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes how to define revenue shares and how to handle billing data: how to restart payment processes and billing runs, preview and export billing data.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../../Shared/reference/c_Certificates.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the usage of certificates for secure communication between <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> and applications integrated with it. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../../Shared/reference/r_ConfigSettings.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> and APP configuration settings.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../../Shared/reference/r_ConfigSettings_OIDC_Tenant.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the properties to be defined for configuring a tenant to connect to an OIDC provider system.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../../Shared/reference/r_LDAP_SettingTypes.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the keys to be defined for enabling access to an organization's LDAP system.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../../Shared/reference/r_Audit_log.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the elements of the audit log. </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../Reference/r_LanguageResourceBundles.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the resources that can be provided and customized in different languages.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../../Shared/reference/r_FileFormat_ImportUsers.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Describes the content and format of a user data file for importing multiple users in one operation.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../../DevelopersGuide/Reference/r_BillingData.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes the elements of an XML file created by exporting customer billing data.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col2"><xref href="../../DevelopersGuide/Reference/r_RevenueShareIntro.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry colname="col3"
                                    >Describes the elements of XML files created by exporting revenue share data.</entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry><xref href="../Reference/r_UserRolesMenuOptions.xml"/></entry>
                                <entry>Gives an overview of the <ph
                                        conref="../../Shared/Product_Name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                                    /> administration portal menu options and the roles required for using them.</entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </table>
            </p>
        </section>
    </conbody>
</concept>
